## Solar Power Ggeneration Forecast
###### Photovoltaic (PV) Solar Power has emerged as the leading source of renewable energy, particularly in India, which benefits from substantial solar insolation. The ongoing advancements in PV module efficiency, battery storage systems, and smart grid technologies have further accelerated the adoption of solar power generation. This surge is due to the decreasing costs and increasing efficiency of solar technology, making it a viable and sustainable option for meeting energy demands. The PV power plants, capable of converting solar radiation into substantial amounts of electrical power, offer a promising future in the energy sector by reducing dependence on fossil fuels and minimizing environmental impact.

###### A PV power plant is essentially a large-scale installation designed to convert sunlight directly into electricity using solar panels. These plants consist of numerous PV modules arranged to maximize sunlight absorption and energy production. The electricity generated is then either stored in batteries or fed into the power grid. The integration of smart grid technology allows for efficient management and distribution of the generated power, ensuring a stable and reliable supply. As solar energy is harnessed directly through these PV panels, it represents a clean and inexhaustible energy source, making it an attractive solution for large-scale power production and contributing significantly to sustainable development goals.

###### We have at hand solar power generation data and weather data of a solar plower plants. Let's explore the given data, draw some insights, try to meet our challenges and predict/forecast the plant output to the extent possible which can be used for a better Grid Management/Stability.
